      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">504.7005</ph> 
         <ph id="lyljga1r"
             rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
             class="- topic/ph ">Notification procedures for cyber-supply chain events</ph>.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li id="lXzEwI" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="pRxQOl" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  <ph id="ezp0o533"
                      rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                      class="- topic/ph ">
                     <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">General</i>.</ph>
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li id="gvis4m3" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="8rh33ac" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <ph id="3h9rfqsn"
                            rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                            class="- topic/ph ">For any potential cyber-supply chain event, including occurrence of an IT security incident, discovery of a prohibited article or source, or identification of supply chain risk information, the contracting officer or another acquisition team member must contact the GSA IT Service Desk by phone at 866-450-5250 or by email at <xref format="html"
                                 href="mailto:ITServiceDesk@gsa.gov"
                                 scope="external"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">ITServiceDesk@gsa.gov</xref>.</ph>
                     </p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li id="gh97zv6" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="biwqrd8" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              <ph id="t9kezosf"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">Do not include source selection sensitive information in the notification to the GSA IT Service Desk.</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                        <li id="3kcnnrl" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="7kcf23ye8" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              <ph id="bribfegfo"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">Do not include other sensitive information (e.g., IP address, access information such as an account login and password) in the notification to the GSA IT Service Desk. The notification should state that additional information is sensitive and will be provided in person or via a secured method.</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                        <li id="gjvoor90y" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="1mvybbs5" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              <ph id="jz6nx9ck"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">Determining whether the identified issue or potential issue is applicable under the procedures for each event type should not delay the acquisition team member from submitting a notification. When unsure, it is better to notify quickly rather than delay the event notification. The GSA IT Service Desk can assist in defining the event type once submitted.</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li id="ezi2nwhd" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="i6ud4ayr" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  <ph id="rbrymx3a"
                      rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                      class="- topic/ph ">
                     <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Occurrence of an IT security incident</i>.</ph>
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li id="c4fca4dn" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="ag0n1r7t" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <ph id="ghw389xb"
                            rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                            class="- topic/ph ">If an IT security incident occurs, concerning any GSA information system or data (owned or operated by GSA or by a contractor or other organization on behalf of GSA), regardless of the estimated value of the contract or order, including purchases under the micro-purchase threshold and purchases using a Government Purchase Card, the contracting officer or another acquisition team member must immediately contact the GSA IT Service Desk.</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li id="8qxlbv8f" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="e6cuaxf" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        <ph id="pjl1j8i9"
                            rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                            class="- topic/ph ">The notification to the GSA IT Service Desk - whether via phone or email - should document as much information as possible, including:</ph>
                     </p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li id="y2ledfqt" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="ch1qg1n" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              <ph id="k6jwb72e"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">Description, date and time of the incident;</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                        <li id="z7xws2bk" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="h7zmja5h" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              <ph id="1x91wph"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">Whether any PII or contractor-attributional information is affected; and</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                        <li id="mr2egknmn" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="ssr9j72c" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              <ph id="sj58u4oj"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">Contract information (contract number, contractor name, name of GSA contracting office), as applicable.</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li id="4wy3wzm" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="x7n1dyn7" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        <ph id="sux32b2"
                            rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                            class="- topic/ph ">Do not delay notifying the GSA IT Service Desk even if all the information requested or considered to be relevant is not available.</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li id="69bs2qcp" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="smxhqn7s" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        <ph id="qcmy1rkv"
                            rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                            class="- topic/ph ">Additional guidance is available from the GSA IT Security Procedural Guide CIO-IT Security-01-02, “Incident Response (IR)”, and GSA IT Security Procedural Guide CIO-IT Security-21-117, “OCISO Cyber Supply Chain Risk Management (C-SCRM) Program”.</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li id="kh0u5frv" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="ltc8qbf" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph>
                        <ph id="6ibx9yto"
                            rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                            class="- topic/ph ">After initial notification, GSA IT may request additional information and will work with the notifier to resolve the issue.</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li id="maclxt9" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="uzgzf59i" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">
                     <ph id="reoj9zg"
                         rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                         class="- topic/ph ">Discovery of a prohibited article or source</ph>
                  </i>.</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li id="lWVNky" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="zeFeMD" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>If a prohibited article <ph id="wvbetcx" rev="" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] ?><?FM MARKER [Why] ?>or source</ph> is discovered within the supply chain of a procurement, <ph id="zkkhpfes" rev="" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] ?><?FM MARKER [Why] ?>regardless of the estimated value of the solicitation, contract, or order, including purchases under the micro-purchase threshold and purchases using a Government Purchase Card,</ph> the contracting officer <ph id="lc1hsv7j"
                            rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                            class="- topic/ph ">or another acquisition team member must</ph> immediately <ph id="u2ir0xhn"
                            rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                            class="- topic/ph ">contact the GSA IT Service Desk</ph>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li id="zMDsAR" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="WgiUWF" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>The <ph id="ttrdutto"
                            rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                            class="- topic/ph ">notification to the GSA IT Service Desk - whether via phone or email - should document as much information as possible, including</ph>:</p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li id="xhvsQL" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="EIGHkS" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>Contract <ph id="fmf74pig" rev="" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] ?><?FM MARKER [Why] ?>or solicitation</ph> information, including contract<ph id="5yw4o14" rev="" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] ?><?FM MARKER [Why] ?> </ph>
                              <ph id="5x8xnibo" rev="" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] ?><?FM MARKER [Why] ?>or solicitation</ph> number<ph id="hz1cf0uf"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">,</ph> contractor <ph id="3omsckf" rev="" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] ?><?FM MARKER [Why] ?>or offeror</ph> name<ph id="vk1ejpgm"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">, and</ph>
                              <ph id="uy6c5ui"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">name of</ph> GSA contracting office;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li id="UKaEHp" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="qbUlDh" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>Prohibited article <ph id="d1hmr8ld"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">or source</ph> name; and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li id="xeXCRc" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="igycct" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>Reason why prohibited article <ph id="gvemknsi"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">or source</ph> is banned on contract.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li id="g6lielgg" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="zk95b0la" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iv)</ph>
                              <ph id="bcc1431"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">) A “critical date,” no less than three (3) business days in the future, for when a response from GSA’s Supply Chain Review Board is requested.</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li id="hx25k6l" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="u555i39v" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        <ph id="7eznapd"
                            rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                            class="- topic/ph ">Do not delay notifying the GSA IT Service Desk even if all the information requested or considered to be relevant is not available.</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li id="q7565gfl" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="eogwebx9" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        <ph id="10mw7rsa"
                            rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                            class="- topic/ph ">After initial notification, GSA’s Supply Chain Review Board may request additional information and will work with the notifier to resolve the issue.</ph>
                     </p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li id="bp5o28l" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="qoau8u4" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              <ph id="mg96xm48"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">If the SCRM Review Board has not responded by the “critical date” required by <xref href="GSAM-i504-7005.dita#i504-7005"
                                       outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                       class="- topic/xref ">504.7005</xref>(c)(2)(iv), the contracting officer may make a determination without the SCRM Review Board’s input, but should seek input and guidance from the appropriate Cyber-Supply Chain Risk Management Policy Advisor (see GSAM <xref href="GSAM-i504-7003.dita#i504-7003"
                                       outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                       class="- topic/xref ">504.7003</xref>(a)) and review additional guidance available on the GSA Acquisition Portal (<xref format="html"
                                       href="http://insite.gsa.gov/cscrm"
                                       scope="external"
                                       class="- topic/xref ">http://insite.gsa.gov/cscrm</xref>) prior to making the determination.</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li id="9fs4ulvd" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="95tx4eaq" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  <ph id="5r9a9tn"
                      rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                      class="- topic/ph ">
                     <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Identification of supply chain risk information</i>.</ph>
               </p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li id="9vd2dty" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="3182oyp" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <ph id="d0csm9xn"
                            rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                            class="- topic/ph ">GSA will share supply chain risk information with the FASC when:</ph>
                     </p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li id="myotc6o" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="mu623ij8" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              <ph id="jzxy8v38"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">The FASC requests information associated with a particular source, a covered article, or a covered procurement (as defined at 41 U.S.C. 4713(k));</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                        <li id="4rj9l3ri" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="4o5ul5dd" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              <ph id="ww32ox7"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">GSA determines that a substantial supply chain risk associated with a source, a covered article, or a covered procurement exists; or</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                        <li id="n7v3y3ut" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="4uswlqty" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph>
                              <ph id="wue5i0p5"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">GSA identifies supply chain risk management information (including both C-SCRM and non-C-SCRM risks) associated with a source, a covered article, or a covered procurement action and such information is deemed relevant to share with the FASC.</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li id="yo74liia" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="544h2u8h" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        <ph id="szcl8f83"
                            rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                            class="- topic/ph ">If substantial supply chain risk information is identified, or the contracting officer or another acquisition team member thinks supply chain risk information should be shared with the FASC, the contracting officer or another acquisition team member must contact the GSA IT Service Desk who will gather relevant information and share it with the appropriate Cyber-Supply Chain Risk Management Policy Advisor.</ph>
                     </p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li id="nisyc89j" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="odkjqk1i" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              <ph id="sb8hjvze"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">Service-level policy may adopt additional procedures to provide acquisition team members with guidance prior to notifying the GSA IT Service Desk.</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li id="2ergpyts" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="glxm1gu" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        <ph id="vzcii93a"
                            rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                            class="- topic/ph ">After initial notification, the appropriate Cyber-Supply Chain Risk Management Policy Advisor may request additional information and will work with the notifier to resolve the issue.</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li id="a7kpzkn" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="0wh1kfya" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        <ph id="ebaz6nj"
                            rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                            class="- topic/ph ">The Cyber-Supply Chain Risk Management Policy Advisors will share information with the Office of Acquisition Policy within OGP. If deemed appropriate, OGP will share the information with the FASC.</ph>
                     </p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li id="isey5uii" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="8cx4kkhr" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              <ph id="vvvkosuh"
                                  rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                                  class="- topic/ph ">The Office of Acquisition Policy within OGP will disseminate any supply chain risk information shared by the FASC to the relevant GSA offices and personnel.</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li id="OzHwUS" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="BrbFJL" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">
                     <ph rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021" class="- topic/ph ">Cyber-</ph>Supply Chain Event Risk Mitigation</i>. The contract administration procedures under <xref format="html"
                        href="https://www.acquisition.gov/content/part-49-termination-contracts"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">FAR part 49</xref> (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">e.g.,</i> cure notice, termination for cause, past performance review) can be u<ph id="0pdqnr4r"
                      rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                      class="- topic/ph ">s</ph>ed as needed to address immediate or future supply chain event concerns. Additional guidance on contract administration procedures is available on the GSA Acquisition Portal (<xref format="html"
                        href="http://insite.gsa.gov/scrm"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">http://insite.gsa.gov/<ph id="dzz788w"
                         rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                         class="- topic/ph ">c</ph>scrm</xref>).</p>
            </li>
            <li id="MBMkZo" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="Onhfoz" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(f)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Past Performance Evaluation</i>. The contracting officer <ph id="6owoos9d"
                      rev="CHANGE 135 SEPTEMBER 28, 2021"
                      class="- topic/ph ">must</ph> report any contractor non-compliance with supply chain requirements within the “Other Areas” portion of any applicable past performance evaluation form.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
